That experience – in finding sudden new barriers to legal immigration to the US – is hardly unique.
During the first nine months of fiscal year 2018, immigration application denials increased by 37% since fiscal year 2016, according to the Cato Institute’s immigration policy analyst David Bier.
On a research mission to Lebanon and Jordan in November, Bell met refugees who had been stranded because of Trump-era policies.
However, experts in immigration policy say there’s no evidence many of the new vetting policies affecting foreign nationals work.
“I think the average American doesn’t know the time, the money and the energy it takes to actually do legal immigration,” Schulman said.